{"id":17847,"title":"Septic cavernous sinus thrombosis due to Campylobacter rectus infection.","abstract":"We report a case of cavernous sinus thrombosis in a 55-year-old Chinese man who presented with headache, ophthalmoplegia and ptosis. Campylobacter rectus was eventually isolated from the blood cultures. He was treated with broad-spectrum antibiotics, anticoagulation and steroids with improvement in his condition. To our knowledge, this is the first documented case of septic cavernous sinus thrombosis caused by C. rectus. ","date":"2014-05-20","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24842357","annotations":[{"name":"Headache","weight":0.799199,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Headache"},{"name":"Sepsis","weight":0.764484,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sepsis"},{"name":"Blood","weight":0.756683,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood"},{"name":"Antibacterial","weight":0.72365,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antibacterial"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Anticoagulant","weight":0.666502,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anticoagulant"},{"name":"Thrombosis","weight":0.616808,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thrombosis"},{"name":"Steroid","weight":0.358033,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steroid"},{"name":"Blood culture","weight":0.287637,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_culture"},{"name":"Cavernous sinus","weight":0.180556,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cavernous_sinus"},{"name":"Ptosis (eyelid)","weight":0.122478,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ptosis_(eyelid)"},{"name":"Campylobacter","weight":0.113142,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Campylobacter"},{"name":"Cavernous sinus thrombosis","weight":0.111412,"wikipedia_article":"htt